deepened%20her%20connection%20with%20audiences%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcharts-which-advertisers-channels-sectors-most-at-risk-tariffs-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eand%C2%A0advertisers%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0beyond%20what%20audio%20can%20afford.%20She%20believes%20seeing%20her%20helps%20the%20audience%20feel%20closer%20to%20her%2C%20and%C2%A0having%20video%20expands%20her%20accessibility%20to%20people%20with%20hearing%20impairments.%20Then%20there's%20the%20ability%20to%20work%20with%20advertisers%20who%20want%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20well%20as%20heard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20add%20video%2C%20you%20really%20open%20the%20door%20to%20the%20brands%20you%20can%20show%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20She%20and%20the%20podcaster%20Kaelyn%20Moore%20now%20cohost%20%26quot%3BClues%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20new%20video-first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-netflix-keeps-seeking-true-crime-shows-despite-lawsuits-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etrue%20crime%3C%2Fa%3E%20podcast%20from%20Max%20Cutler's%20Pave%20Studios.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPodcasting%20has%20never%20been%20bigger.%20It's%20credited%20with%20helping%20shape%20the%20presidential%20election.%20Big%20Tech%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famazon-wondery-launches-toy-line-wow-in-the-world-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecoming%20for%20its%20piece%20of%20the%20pie%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20now%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnetflix-eyeing-video-podcasts-creators-next-growth-act-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Evideo%20is%20transforming%20the%20medium%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20people%20increasingly%20prefer%20to%20watch%20their%20favorite%20hosts%2C%20helping%20people%20like%20Absher%20build%20careers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYouTube%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fblog.google%2Ffeed%2Fyoutube-podcast-listeners%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20February%20that%20more%20than%201%20billion%20people%20listened%20to%20podcasts%20on%20the%20platform%20every%20month%20and%20that%20in%202024%2C%20viewers%20watched%20over%20400%20million%20hours%20of%20podcasts%20monthly%20on%20TVs.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.edisonresearch.com%2Fyoutube-is-the-preferred-podcast-listening-service%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEdison%20Research%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20in%20October%20that%20YouTube%20had%20become%20the%20top%20podcast%20consumption%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rise%20of%20video%20pods%20has%20even%20led%20to%20debate%20over%20the%20question%3A%20How%20do%20you%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frise-of-video-podcasts-complications-confusion-advertisers-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edefine%20a%20podcast%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20anyway%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20one%20thing%20that's%20not%20up%20for%20debate%20is%20that%20video%20has%20expanded%20the%20market%20and%20job%20opportunities%20in%20podcasting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d629df77-66b5-412a-8f8e-c0a614b8eabc%5C%22%3EIt's%20not%20just%20hosts%20who%20are%20benefiting%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EVideo%20podcasting's%20growth%20has%20created%20opportunity%20for%20people%20in%20a%20medium%20that's%20traditionally%20had%20a%20low%20barrier%20for%20entry%20but%20rarely%20is%20a%20full-time%20job.%20Along%20with%20podcasters%20like%20Absher%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finfluencers-are-using-podcasts-to-reinvent-themselves-earn-more-money-2025-2https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finfluencers-are-using-podcasts-to-reinvent-themselves-earn-more-money-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esocial%20media%20creators%20are%20increasingly%3C%2Fa%3E%20getting%20in%20on%20the%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20creating%20opportunities%20for%20service%20firms%20like%20Podglomerate%20and%20Creator%20Science%20that%20help%20hosts%20translate%20their%20shows%20to%20the%20screen%2C%20as%20well%20as%20digital%20media%20and%20Hollywood%20folks%20whose%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-hurt-hollywood-hopes-for-tv-movie-recovery-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etraditional%20sources%20of%20work%20are%20drying%20up%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPodglomerate%20is%20hiring%20people%20including%20motion%20graphics%20editors%2C%20animators%2C%20scriptwriters%2C%20and%20even%20composers%2C%20said%20Chris%20Boniello%2C%20who%20came%20out%20of%20video%20and%20now%20runs%20production%20for%20the%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20do%20think%20it's%20going%20to%20bring%20a%20lot%20more%20people%20into%20the%20space%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20wouldn't%20be%20surprised%20if%20you%20see%20TV%20editors%20with%20multicamera%20skills%20coming%20into%20podcasting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYouTube%20and%20Spotify%20are%20helping%20grow%20the%20field%2C%20with%20creators%20eager%20to%20cash%20in%20on%20video's%20much-bigger%20revenue%20pie.%20EMARKETER%20expects%20advertisers%20to%20spend%20some%20%24108%20billion%20on%20digital%20video%20in%202025%2C%20versus%20about%20%242.5%20billion%20being%20spent%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.emarketer.com%2Flearningcenter%2Fguides%2Fthe-podcast-industry-report-statistics%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaudio%20podcast%20advertising%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYouTube%2C%20with%20its%20massive%20scale%20and%20powerful%20algorithm%2C%20can%20be%20a%20great%20discovery%20engine%2C%20solving%20a%20problem%20that%20has%20long%20vexed%20the%20medium.%20Podcasters%20also%20like%20that%20YouTube%20keeps%20people%20watching%20by%20serving%20them%20more%20episodes.%20Spotify%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20is%20promoting%20short%20video%20clips%20to%20entice%20people%20to%20tune%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20advertisers%2C%20SiriusXM%20recently%20rolled%20out%20Creator%20Connect%2C%20a%20tool%20that%20creates%20different%20versions%20of%20a%20podcast%20ad%20for%20video%20and%20social%20media.%20Gabe%20Tartaglia%2C%20who%20heads%20podcast%20and%20satellite%20sales%20for%20SiriusXM%2C%20has%20said%20that%20the%20company%20has%20heard%20from%20advertisers%20that%20they%20want%20to%20be%20able%20to%20buy%20against%20hosts'%20multiplatform%20efforts.%20About%2012%25%20of%20SiriusXM's%20podcast%20advertisers%20are%20already%20running%20ads%20on%20more%20than%20one%20format%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJay%20Clouse%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20Creator%20Science%2C%20said%20his%20own%20video%20podcast%20grossed%20%2460%2C000%20in%20revenue%20in%202024%20between%20programmatic%20ads%20on%20YouTube%20and%20brand%20integrations%20%E2%80%94%20triple%20what%20it%20was%20making%20in%202022%20as%20an%20audio-only%20podcast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Claire%20Parker%20and%20Ashley%20Hamilton%20of%20the%20podcast%20%26quot%3BCelebrity%20Memoir%20Book%20Club.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F680a9712c6ad288d147f155b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EClaire%20Parker%20and%20Ashley%20Hamilton%20of%20the%20podcast%20%26quot%3BCelebrity%20Memoir%20Book%20Club.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3EJuan%20Carlos%20Quimper%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b3fa30f6-ef3e-4349-ab6d-01a0e1c11b01%5C%22%3E'No%20doubt%20video%20has%20increased%20the%20cost'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rise%20of%20video%20has%20raised%20the%20once%20low%20barrier%20to%20entry%20for%20podcasting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20people%20could%20make%20a%20show%20with%20as%20little%20as%20a%20phone%2C%20full%20productions%20with%20everything%20from%20location%20rental%2C%20hair%2C%20and%20makeup%20can%20cost%20as%20much%20as%20%2410%2C000%20a%20shoot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20YouTube%20comes%20opportunity%20but%20also%20competition.%20To%20stand%20out%20quickly%20from%20the%20millions%20of%20other%20creators%2C%20you%20have%20to%20work%20hard%20to%20optimize%20your%20title%2C%20thumbnail%2C%20and%20format%2C%20Clouse%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou're%20still%20auditioning%20for%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20might%20listen%20for%2060%20seconds%20and%20leave.%20So%20the%20first%2030%20seconds%2C%20two%20minutes%2C%20has%20to%20be%20retentive.%20You%20need%20to%20think%20about%20the%20title%20and%20thumb%20before%20you%20record.%20It%20needs%20to%20be%20attention-grabbing%2C%20and%20you%20need%20to%20know%20what%20the%20package%20is%20going%20to%20be.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EForever%20Dog%20Productions%2C%20a%20podcast%20studio%20founded%20in%202016%20and%20known%20for%20its%20work%20with%20comedians%20like%20Bowen%20Yang%20of%20%26quot%3BSaturday%20Night%20Live%26quot%3B%20and%20Ayo%20Edebiri%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Bear%2C%26quot%3B%20went%20all%20in%20on%20video%20in%202023.%20Growing%20on%20YouTube%20has%20meant%20a%20lot%20of%20testing%20and%20studying%20things%20like%20retention%20and%20watch%20time%20to%20find%20the%20audience.%20It%20also%20more%20than%20doubles%20the%20number%20of%20people%20required.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20half-ass%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Joe%20Cilio%2C%20one%20of%20Forever%20Dog's%20founders%2C%20said.%20%26quot%3BNo%20doubt%20video%20has%20increased%20the%20cost%20and%20amount%20of%20personnel.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20coming%20from%20traditional%20TV%20and%20film%2C%20a%20reality%20check%20can%20await.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSometimes%20the%20Hollywood%20people%20have%20to%20downshift%20because%20they're%20used%20to%20television%20and%20now%20they're%20in%20digital%20media%2C%26quot%3B%20Cilio%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20smaller%20potatoes%3B%20it's%20less%20money.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHosts%20who%20are%20used%20to%20the%20cozy%20embrace%20of%20their%20listeners%20can%20likewise%20be%20unprepared%20for%20the%20negative%20comments%20that%20can%20come%20with%20being%20on%20YouTube%20and%20beyond%2C%20where%20making%20snarky%20remarks%20is%20as%20easy%20as%20hitting%20play.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPodcast%20people%20like%20being%20pod-famous%2C%20but%20then%20you%20start%20putting%20them%20on%20Facebook%20%E2%80%94%20people%20are%20crazy%2C%26quot%3B%20Cilio%20said.%20%26quot%3BTalent%20can%20take%20the%20comments%20so%20hard.%20The%20price%20of%20engagement%20can%20weigh%20heavily%20because%20people%20don't%20want%20to%20be%20criticized.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20New%20York%20comedians%20Claire%20Parker%20and%20Ashley%20Hamilton%20host%20the%20podcast%20%26quot%3BCelebrity%20Memoir%20Book%20Club%2C%26quot%3B%20a%20part%20of%20Vox%20Media%2C%20on%20which%20they%20discuss%20celebrity%20memoirs.%20They've%20seen%20the%20discovery%20and%20revenue%20benefits%20of%20video%20but%20acknowledge%20the%20downsides%2C%20like%20the%20expense%20and%20emphasis%20on%20visuals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20look%20a%20certain%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20Parker%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20not%20why%20I%20got%20into%20podcasting%2C%20to%20look%20Alex%20Cooper-beautiful.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvideo-podcasting-growing-creating-work-for-hollywood-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1750883314000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681bc34b3fe8d39283653b2d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvideo-podcasting-growing-creating-work-for-hollywood-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Video%20is%20transforming%20podcasting%20as%20consumers%20increasingly%20prefer%20watching%20their%20favorite%20hosts.%20It's%20also%20helping%20people%20build%20careers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22lmoses%40insider.c