BThe%20truth%20is%2C%20if%20you're%20cutting%20corners%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20catch%20up%20to%20you%20at%20some%20point.%20And%20that's%20what%20we%20hear%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPecrkill%20spoke%20with%20Business%20Insider%20about%20how%20those%20running%20organizations%20should%20think%20about%20the%20values%20they%20maintain%20as%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBusiness%20Insider%3A%20What%20shapes%20your%20thinking%20around%20ethical%20leadership%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrian%20Peckrill%3A%20What%20Bill%20McGowan%2C%20our%20benefactor%2C%20saw%20is%20that%20when%20a%20business%20lacked%20ethics%20and%20they%20were%20fully%20focused%20on%20profits%2C%20what%20suffered%20was%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETen%20years%20after%20Bill%20died%2C%20MCI%20and%20WorldCom%20got%20wiped%20out%20by%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvaleant-is-not-enron-its-worldcom-2016-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emassive%20accounting%20scandal%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Those%20who%20worked%20for%20MCI%20became%20millionaires%20because%20of%20their%20success%20at%20MCI%2C%20and%20if%20they%20didn't%20cash%20out%20prior%20to%20the%20bankruptcy%2C%20they%20lost%20everything.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20it%20was%20very%20clear%20to%20our%20board%20that%20ethical%20leadership%20transforms%20lives%20%E2%80%94%20that%20this%20is%20not%20just%20a%20matter%20of%20what's%20good%20for%20society.%20It's%20good%20for%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20need%20to%20create%20leaders%20who%2C%20when%20making%20decisions%2C%20look%20to%20their%20values.%20They%20are%20transparent.%20They're%20accountable%20to%20the%20people%20that%20they%20work%20for.%20They're%20accountable%20to%20their%20clients.%20They%20are%20they%20have%20integrity.%20They're%20thinking%20about%20how%20their%20words%20and%20their%20actions%20align%2C%20and%20they're%20empathetic%20to%20the%20ways%20that%20people%20struggle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIf%20you%20look%20at%20a%20metric%20like%20the%20Edelman%20Trust%20Barometer%2C%20there's%20been%20a%20slide%20in%20workers'%20trust%20in%20their%20employers.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20shocking%20to%20see%20how%20it's%20fallen%20off.%20I've%20been%20thinking%20about%20this%20a%20lot%20in%20regard%20to%20the%20not-for-profit%20sector%2C%20which%20the%20data%20is%20a%20little%20bit%20stronger%20on.%20What%20I%20keep%20coming%20back%20to%20is%20that%20to%20be%20a%20trusted%20entity%2C%20ethical%20leadership%20matters%20because%20it%20means%20that%20your%20actions%20and%20your%20words%20align%2C%20and%20that%20you%20can%20get%20trust%20by%20being%20empathetic%20and%20credible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Brian%20Peckrill%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F685aabe685e81483682ca401%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPeckrill%20encourages%20CEOs%20of%20for-profit%20companies%20can%20benefit%20by%20%26quot%3Bleading%20with%20your%20values.%26quot%3B%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20William%20G.%20McGowan%20Charitable%20Fund%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWith%20AI%20threatening%20jobs%2C%20is%20rebuilding%20trust%20now%20a%20bigger%20challenge%20for%20for-profit%20CEOs%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wouldn't%20say%20that%20I%20think%20it's%20harder%20now.%20Society%20is%20constantly%20going%20through%20cycles%20of%20innovation.%20The%20way%20that%20our%20business%20leadership%20and%20education%20have%20progressed%20has%20put%20more%20and%20more%20of%20an%20emphasis%20on%20profit%20maximization.%20You%20look%20at%20MBA%20programs%2C%20and%20when%20they%20were%20founded%2C%20they%20were%20deeply%20philosophical.%20They%20were%20about%20building%20a%20whole-minded%20individual%20who%20can%20think%20broadly%20about%20business%2C%20and%20over%20time%2C%20they%20became%20more%20focused%20on%20the%20mathematical%20economics%20of%20making%20profits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20you've%20maxed%20out%20efficiencies%2C%20the%20only%20place%20to%20go%20is%20either%20breaking%20the%20law%20or%20harming%20people.%20We%20need%20to%20return%20to%20that%20holistic%20way%20of%20thinking.%20Part%20of%20that%20is%20asking%20not%20can%20we%2C%20but%20should%20we%3F%20What's%20the%20effect%20on%20people%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20look%20at%20the%20most%20trusted%20businesses%20%E2%80%94%20those%20that%20are%20using%20ethical%20leadership%20as%20a%20frame%20%E2%80%94%20their%20horizon%20of%20profits%20is%20greater.%20Those%20businesses%20that%20think%20about%20their%20people%2C%20think%20about%20how%20they%20can%20invest%20in%20their%20people%2C%20and%20are%20not%20just%20focused%20on%20short-term%20profits%20through%20efficiencies%2C%20do%20better%20in%20the%20long%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20lessons%20can%20for-profit%20CEOs%20learn%20from%20nonprofit%20leaders%20about%20building%20trust%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20major%20element%20to%20this%20is%20that%20when%20I%20say%20independence%20in%20the%20not-for-profit%20sector%2C%20this%20means%20leading%20with%20your%20values.%20It's%20setting%20up%20a%20charter%20between%20your%20stakeholders%20in%20your%20organization%20that%20you're%20going%20to%20deliver%20on%20a%20certain%20mission%20and%20that%20you're%20going%20to%20invest%20your%20money%20in%20this%20type%20of%20approach.%20I%20don't%20think%20it's%20very%20different%20for%20the%20for-profit%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20people%20align%20themselves%20with%20an%20organization%2C%20they're%20expecting%20the%20organization%20to%20live%20up%20to%20their%20values.%20It's%20when%20organizations%20lack%20integrity%20and%20they%20fail%20to%20live%20up%20to%20the%20values%20that%20they%20put%20on%20their%20website%20and%20that%20they%20posture%20through%20media%2C%20that%20people%20lose%20trust%20in%20organizations.%20And%20I%20think%20that%20the%20for-profit%20sector%20could%20learn%20some%20lessons%20from%20not-for-profits%20in%20this%20regard.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusiness-leaders-focused-on-ethics-do-better-mcgowan-director-2025-6%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1750882460000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F685aacce85e81483682ca42e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusiness-leaders-focused-on-ethics-do-better-mcgowan-director-2025-6%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ethical%20leadership%20and%20investing%20in%20people%20can%20drive%20long-term%20profits%2C%20says%20Brian%20Peckrill%20of%20the%20McGowan%20Charitable%20Fund.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tparadis%40businessinsider.com%20(Tim%20Paradis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbusiness-leaders-focused-on-ethics-do-better-mcgowan-director-2025-6%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Rolling%20Stones%20Cover%20Clifton%20Chenier%2C%20King%20of%20Zydeco%2C%20to%20Mark%20His%20Centenary%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1750882264000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F06%2FGettyImages-2161968958-e1750881921706.jpg%3Fcrop%3D0px%252C14px%252C2428px%252C1366px%26resize%3D1000%252C563%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F%3Fp%3D1236440497%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Rolling%20Stones%20are%20once%20again%20waving%20the%20flag%20of%20their%20musical%20forebears%20with%20a%20cover%20of%20Clifton%20Chenier%E2%80%99s%20zydeco%20tune%20%E2%80%9CZydeco%20Sont%20Pas%20Sal%C3%A9s.%E2%80%9D%20Chenier%2C%20an%20accord