ulius-developers-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20to%20transform%20the%20workplace%3C%2Fa%3E.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mckinsey.com%2Fcapabilities%2Fmckinsey-digital%2Four-insights%2Fsuperagency-in-the-workplace-empowering-people-to-unlock-ais-full-potential-at-work%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20McKinsey%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20compared%20the%20tech%20to%20the%20birth%20of%20the%20internet%20and%20the%20arrival%20of%20the%20steam%20engine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20its%20reality%20is%20still%20taking%20shape.%20AI%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-usage-in-workplace-statistics-gallup-poll-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadoption%20is%3C%2Fa%3E%20inconsistent%20at%20most%20organizations%2C%20workers%20have%20varying%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-prevent-employee-skepticism-push-back-gen-ai-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elevels%20of%20interest%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20there's%20often%20a%20difference%20between%20AI%20buzz%20and%20its%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-ai-strategies-early-stages-lattice-ceo-sarah-franklin-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epractical%20application%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarGurus%2C%20an%20online%20marketplace%20for%20buying%20and%20selling%20cars%2C%20is%20one%20company%20trying%20to%20bridge%20that%20divide.%20Last%20October%2C%20it%20launched%20AI%20Forward%2C%20a%2020-person%20working%20group%20that%20brings%20together%20leaders%20across%20departments%2C%20including%20product%2C%20engineering%2C%20legal%2C%20and%20sales.%20The%20group's%20goal%20is%20to%20identify%20the%20right%20applications%20for%20AI%2C%20evaluate%20potential%20tools%2C%20and%20encourage%20employee%20experimentation%20through%20workshops%2C%20one-on-one%20guidance%2C%20and%20pilot%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20everyone%20has%20to%20figure%20out%20AI%20tools%20on%20their%20own%2C%20we%20risk%20losing%20interest%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sarah%20Rich%2C%20a%20senior%20principal%20data%20scientist%20at%20CarGurus%20and%20a%20lead%20coordinator%20of%20AI%20Forward.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20trying%20to%20offer%20cheat%20sheets%20and%20share%20what's%20working.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20added%20that%20once%20employees%20see%20how%20AI%20can%20make%20their%20day-to-day%20more%20efficient%20or%20offer%20new%20approaches%2C%20they%20tend%20to%20get%20on%20board.%20%26quot%3BWe%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20that%20when%20we%20ask%20people%20to%20invest%20time%20in%20AI%2C%20they're%20going%20to%20quickly%20see%20a%20reward.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERich%20spoke%20with%20Business%20Insider%20about%20how%20AI%20Forward%20is%20helping%20employees%20gain%20the%20confidence%20to%20explore%20the%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20clarity%20and%20length.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBusiness%20Insider%3A%20What%20was%20the%20reason%20for%20AI%20Forward%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESarah%20Rich%3A%20There's%20a%20lot%20of%20pressure%20to%20get%20ahead%20with%20AI.%20And%20I%20imagine%20this%20is%20the%20case%20at%20many%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20there's%20a%20sense%20that%20if%20you%20don't%20keep%20up%2C%20you're%20leaving%20innovation%20on%20the%20table.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20there's%20a%20gap%20between%20the%20excitement%20around%20AI%20and%20understanding%20what%20it%20means%20for%20each%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20started%20AI%20Forward%20to%20meet%20every%20business%20unit%20and%20function%20where%20they%20are.%20The%20group%20works%20together%20to%20evaluate%20use%20cases%20and%20AI%20tools%2C%20which%20is%20key%20given%20how%20fast%20AI%20is%20evolving%20and%20the%20constant%20onslaught%20of%20capabilities.%20The%20group%20also%20offers%20structured%20support%20to%20help%20employees%20learn%20how%20to%20use%20the%20tools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20often%20does%20the%20group%20meet%2C%20and%20what%20was%20your%20first%20order%20of%20business%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20meet%20monthly%20as%20a%20group%2C%20and%20in%20between%2C%20there%20are%20focused%20sessions%20within%20their%20respective%20departments.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20first%20things%20I%20did%20was%20meet%20individually%20with%20leaders%20to%20help%20identify%20a%20few%20solid%20use%20cases%20that%20could%20really%20move%20the%20needle%20for%20their%20teams.%20Some%20were%20ready%20to%20go%3B%20others%20had%20no%20idea%20where%20to%20start.%20We%20spent%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20brainstorming%2C%20understanding%20where%20the%20underlying%20tech%20is%2C%20and%20recognizing%20that%20in%20some%20functions%2C%20the%20tech%20just%20isn't%20there%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20other%20functions%2C%20like%20coding%20tools%20in%20engineering%20or%20natural%20language-based%20solutions%20for%20reviewing%20contracts%20in%20legal%2C%20the%20tools%20are%20ready.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20happens%20next%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20carve%20out%20time%20and%20space%20for%20people%20to%20experiment.%20For%20our%20engineering%20teams%2C%20we%20run%20office%20hours%20and%20jam%20sessions%2C%20which%20are%20essentially%20open%20collaborations%2C%20to%20help%20people%20learn%20coding%20tools%2C%20like%20Cursor%20and%20Windsurf.%20We%20also%20held%20an%20AI%20coding%20week%20to%20help%20everyone%20start%20using%20an%20AI%20tool%20on%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELLM%20solutions%20are%20effective%20for%20language-focused%20work%20that's%20labor%20intensive.%20When%20teams%20experiment%20with%20those%20tools%2C%20they%20see%20their%20work%20accelerate%20quickly.%20We%20make%20time%20for%20experimentation%3B%20it%20doesn't%20just%20happen.%20But%20usually%20people%20see%20something%20that%20impresses%20them%2C%20and%20AI%20starts%20to%20sell%20itself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat's%20the%20group%20doing%20to%20support%20employees%20who%20are%20less%20open%20to%20AI%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20are%20at%20different%20places%20on%20the%20adoption%20and%20enthusiasm%20curve.%20Some%20are%20excited%20about%20an%20open-ended%20jam%20session.%20Others%20need%20structure%2C%20where%20they're%20required%20to%20try%20a%20tool%20on%20ticketed%20work%2C%20or%20assigned%20tasks%20or%20projects%2C%20and%20get%20help%20as%20they%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20group%20has%20learned%20that%20we%20need%20offerings%20at%20different%20levels.%20It's%20important%20that%20everyone%20comes%20along%20to%20some%20degree%2C%20but%20not%20everyone%20is%20going%20to%20have%20the%20same%20level%20of%20zeal%2C%20and%20that's%20OK.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20are%20you%20measuring%20success%20for%20AI%20Forward%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20tracking%20several%20metrics%3A%20how%20often%20people%20use%20AI%2C%20which%20tools%20they%20use%2C%20their%20confidence%20in%20using%20them%20safely%2C%20and%20their%20overall%20sentiment%20about%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20often%20a%20focus%20on%20adoption%20in%20terms%20of%20efficiency%20or%20hours%20saved%2C%20but%20people%20tend%20to%20misjudge%20that.%20AI%20might%20not%20always%20save%20time%2C%20but%20it%20might%20help%20you%20create%20a%20better%20product%20because%20you%20explored%20six%20different%20directions%20to%20test%20options%20before%20feeling%20confident%20you've%20landed%20on%20the%20best%20one.%20We're%20careful%20about%20sentiment%20because%20AI%20is%20disruptive%20and%20can%20feel%20threatening.%20Pushing%20AI%20without%20acknowledging%20that%20nuance%20feels%20tone%20deaf.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20have%20you%20learned%20from%20AI%20Forward%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe've%20seen%20patterns%20emerge%20in%20our%20data%20in%20three%20phases.%20First%2C%20people%20feel%20enthusiastic%20because%20they've%20been%20told%20AI%20is%20magic%20and%20will%20solve%20everything.%20Then%2C%20there's%20this%20middle-ground%20disillusionment%2C%20where%20people%20have%20had%20some%20interaction%20with%20AI%20tools%2C%20but%20they%20haven't%20worked%20or%20lived%20up%20to%20the%20hype.%20There's%20a%20narrative%20around%20AI%20replacing%20jobs%20versus%20augmenting%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ideal%20third%20phase%20comes%20when%20people%20start%20to%20use%20AI%20and%20don't%20feel%20threatened%20by%20it.%20They%20see%20that%20it%20makes%20them%20better%20at%20their%20job.%20They%20also%20get%20that%20without%20real%20people%2C%20AI%20can't%20do%20meaningful%2C%20impactful%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESentiment%20depends%20on%20where%20the%20individual%20or%20team%20is%20in%20their%20adoption%20effort%20and%20how%20successful%20they've%20been%20at%20finding%20the%20right%20use%20cases.%20Based%20on%20internal%20data%20ranging%20from%20the%20use%20of%20enterprise-wide%20AI%20productivity%20tools%2C%20procurement%20requests%20for%20new%20AI%20products%2C%20and%20anecdotes%20across%20teams%2C%20it's%20clear%20that%20a%20vast%20majority%20of%20employees%20have%2C%20at%20minimum%2C%20tried%20AI%20in%20their%20day-to-day%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat's%20your%20advice%20for%20companies%20that%20want%20to%20start%20similar%20AI%20working%20groups%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20AI%20is%20novel%20in%20many%20ways%2C%20especially%20in%20how%20it%20affects%20people%20psychologically%20and%20emotionally%2C%20it's%20also%20pretty%20familiar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20there's%20a%20tendency%20to%20get%20caught%20up%20in%20technology%2C%20the%20real%20challenge%20is%20the%20humans.%20I%20recommend%20focusing%20on%20them%3A%20bring%20people%20together%2C%20make%20them%20feel%20safe%2C%20and%20give%20them%20a%20reason%20and%20a%20space%20to%20pay%20attention.%20It%20needs%20to%20feel%20good%20and%20encouraging%2C%20not%20alienating.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%