status%2F1239385530493591554%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EMarch%2016%2C%202020%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETake%20the%20case%20shared%20by%20Indian%20Forest%20Service%20(IFS)%20officer%20Parveen%20Kaswan%20in%20Shivpuri%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh.%20A%20young%20leopard%20had%20accidentally%20fallen%20into%20a%2025-foot-deep%20well%20in%20a%20farming%20village.%20Instead%20of%20turning%20the%20site%20into%20a%20spectacle%2C%20villagers%20did%20exactly%20what%20they%20were%20supposed%20to%20%E2%80%93%20they%20called%20the%20forest%20department%2C%20stood%20back%2C%20and%20waited.%20In%20a%20post%20that%20went%20viral%20for%20the%20right%20reasons%2C%20Kaswan%20shared%20images%20of%20the%20rescue%20operation%2C%20writing%3A%20%E2%80%9CPeople%20did%20not%20panic.%20They%20secured%20the%20place.%20Forest%20staff%20came%20and%20rescued%20the%20leopard%20without%20any%20injury.%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FParveenKaswan%2Fstatus%2F1239385530493591554%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20video%20showed%20the%20leopard%20calmly%3C%2Fa%3E%20climbing%20into%20the%20crate%20that%20was%20lowered%20%E2%80%94%20a%20moment%20that%20was%20only%20possible%20because%20the%20crowd%20had%20stayed%20quiet%20and%20cooperative.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENilgiri%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20example%20came%20from%20Nilgiris%20district%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20where%20a%20herd%20of%20elephants%20wandered%20close%20to%20a%20tea%20estate.%20Instead%20of%20trying%20to%20chase%20them%20or%20take%20selfies%2C%20residents%20quickly%20informed%20the%20forest%20department%20and%20allowed%20the%20herd%20to%20retreat%20calmly.%20IFS%20officer%20Supriya%20Sahu%2C%20Additional%20Chief%20Secretary%20of%20Environment%2C%20Climate%20Change%20and%20Forests%2C%20later%20shared%20the%20story%20on%20X%20%2C%20praising%20local%20communities%20for%20t